'''9 to 5''' is a phrase which refers to the time at which some office employees work each day. These hours are the standard business hours in the [[United States]] and are an incarnation of the [[eight-hour day]].  The term ''9 to 5'' is also used as a [[slang]] term for a day job; for example, "My ''9 to 5'' is at a law office, but my real love is playing in the band."

The phrase became the title of two different songs: [[9 to 5 (Dolly Parton song)|9 to 5]] by [[Dolly Parton]] and [[9 to 5 (Sheena Easton song)|9 to 5]] by [[Sheena Easton]], which had the title “Morning Train (9 to 5)” for its North American release.

Also refers to the name of a 1980 movie (specifically [[Nine to Five]]) starring [[Dolly Parton]], [[Jane Fonda]], and [[Lily Tomlin]], for which Parton's above-referenced song served as a theme song.  The movie was followed by a short lived TV series called 9 to 5.

